title: Population density in Texas 1960 to 2018
yAxis: Number of residents per square mile
summary: This is a line chart with an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Number of residents per square mile, containing a total of 13 data points.
In general Number of residents per square mile has rose over the Year.
Number of residents per square mile is slightly increasing from 1960 to 2010, and lastly roughly constant from 2010 to 2018.
The most drastic increase took place within the Year 2000 and 2010.
The highest Number of residents per square mile, of value 109.9 was reached at Year 2018
Minimum Number of residents per square mile about 36.6 was reached at Year 1960
